criteria.textblock:
        Inclusion Criteria:

          -  adult patients, >= 18 years of age;

          -  chronic renal anemia;

          -  continuous stable iv or sc maintenance epoetin therapy during previous 4 weeks;

          -  regular long-term hemodialysis therapy with the same mode of dialysis for previous 3
             months.

        Exclusion Criteria:

          -  transfusion of red blood cells during previous 2 months;

          -  poorly controlled hypertension requiring hospitalization or interruption of epoetin
             treatment in previous 6 months;

          -  significant acute or chronic bleeding.
